To kick off the new year，... North Korea revealed that it′s leader Kim Jong－un paid homage to his father and grandfather at the Kumsusan Palace of the Sun. 
But aside from that， little else is known.
What bout his priorities and who will be by his side.
According to our Connie Kim， analysts are looking between the lines for clues. 
When Kim Jong－un visited the Kumsuan Palace of the Sun in Pyongyang on the first day of 2016，...
standing to his far right was Jo Yon－jun ， a first deputy of the ruling Workers′ Party′s Organization and Guidance Department. 
It was the first time Jo was spotted in the first row... with party secretaries who sit much higher up on the power ladder.
The 75－year－old is known to be in charge of executing senior officials， and his placement in last Friday′s line－up is grabbing attention because it coincided with the North Korean leader′s New Year′s speech which focused on efforts to root out corruption.
″We must intensely fight against corruption， bureaucracy， and forces that disrupt unity among our workers.″
Other officials that took the front rows were army politburo chief Hwang Pyong－so ， defense chief Pak Yong－sik ， the Korean People′s Army chief of general staff Ri Yong－gil ， and state security minister Kim Won－hong . 
Experts say these men will likely remain as close aides to leader Kim this year. 
″The timing of this change can be seen as top officials pledging full support of the Kim Jong－un regime ahead of the 7th Congress of the Workers′ Party of Korea.″ 
What′s also noteworthy is an apparent shift in Kim′s priorit...
