황병서•오극렬•리용무 제재…북한 黨•軍 핵심인사 조준
The United States is taking the initiative on pressuring the North by blacklisting key North Korean figures and entities under its own unilateral sanctions.
They include top aides to Kim Jong-un and the regime\'s powerful National Defense Commission.
The commission was among eleven individuals and five entities included on the U.S. sanctions list. 
The four other entities include the Academy of National Defense Science, the Ministry of Atomic Energy Industry, the National Aerospace Development Administration and the Central Military Commission of the Workers\' Party of Korea.
The individuals include Hwang Pyong-so , director of the general political bureau of the Korean People\'s Army and Defense Minister Pak Yong-sik , as well as the vice chairmen of the defense commission.
In a related development, the European Union is considering imposing addition sanctions on North Korea.
Federica Mogherini, the EU\'s foreign policy chief added that Pyongyang\'s actions were \"a grave threat to international peace and security in the region and beyond.\" 

