North Korea\'s state media is reporting that the country\'s senior official for inter-Korean affairs, Kim Yang-gon, died in car accident early yesterday morning.
For more we connect live to our unification ministry correspondent Connie Kim.
Connie, what can you tell us about Kim\'s death?

Mark, North Korea\'s Korean Central News Agency says Kim Yang-gon, a secretary of the ruling Workers\' Party of Korea and a member of the party\'s Central Committee Politbureau, died in a car accident at 6:15 a.m. on Tuesday morning.rtzzzee
He was 73.
Kim was one of the closest aides to North Korean leader Kim Jong-un and was in charge of handling inter-Korean relations.
The KCNA report says Kim Jong-un will lead a state funeral for the deceased on Thursday.
Choe Ryong-hae, a senior secretary in the Workers\' Party who had been out of the public eye,... has been listed as a member of the funeral committee,... implying he has been reinstated.

Kim Yang-gon may seem familiar to those who follow inter-Korean affairs...
He contributed to pulling the two Koreas back from brink of conflict after a landmine explosion near the inter-Korean border in August... that Seoul blames on Pyongyang.
He also played a leading role in bringing about a 2007 summit between then North Korean leader Kim Jong-il and South Korean President Roh Moo-hyun.

Kim Yang-gon played a key role in inter-Korean ties. What effect will his death have on relations between the two Koreas?

Kim was considered a dove in his handling of cross-border affairs... and the general consensus seems to be that his death...
